<div type="apparatus">
<head>Apparatus</head>
<p>The cutter had to avoid a hole in l. 3.</p>
</div>
<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>To the goddess Aphrodite, to the Imperator Hadrian Augustus son of the god Trajan, grandson of the god Nerva, to the People: Pereitas Attalos son of Zenon the son of Zenon dedicated the <seg cert="low">decoration</seg> of the doorway at his own expense.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>The same text was inscribed on the north-east doorway (<xref type="inscription" n="1558" href="050208">5.208</xref> =Mendel, 168b) with differences in layout and a different hand.</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
<head>Locations</head>
<p>
<rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">Hadrianic Baths, East Court</rs>: Fallen at the south doorway of the East Court of the Hadrianic Baths, connecting the Galerie de l'Est with the south portico of the court.</rs>
<rs type="origLocation"><rs type="monuList">Hadrianic Baths, East Court</rs>: over the door.</rs>
<rs type="lastLocation">Findspot</rs>
</p>
</div>
